Daniel Koh is an accomplished cybersecurity professional with over 3.5 years of experience as a Cyber Security Manager at United Overseas Bank Malaysia. 
In this role, he has demonstrated exceptional leadership in safeguarding critical information systems, managing security operations, 
and implementing robust cybersecurity frameworks to mitigate emerging threats. His expertise lies in identifying vulnerabilities, developing comprehensive risk management strategies, 
and ensuring compliance with regulatory standards, which are crucial in the fast-paced financial sector.

With a strong academic foundation, Daniel holds a Bachelor’s Degree with first-class honours in Computer Networking and Security from Lancaster University and has passed the prestigious ISC2 CISSP exam, 
underscoring his deep technical knowledge and commitment to excellence. He is currently pursuing a Master’s in Cybersecurity at Universiti Malaya, 
further solidifying his expertise and staying abreast of the latest advancements in the field.

Daniel’s passion for exploring the unknown in cybersecurity drives his innovative approach to problem-solving. 
He excels at bridging technical complexities with strategic objectives, ensuring that security solutions align with organizational goals. 
His data-driven mindset and ability to craft frameworks tailored to dynamic environments position him as a thought leader in the ever-evolving cybersecurity landscape.






